// IF-159 minimal repro: assigning the SAME waveform to two CT indices
// triggers a clean "already assigned index" error in the original
// binary, but causes the recon to ABORT with `terminate called without
// an active exception` (worker exit -6).
//
// The recon should produce the same graceful error, not crash.

wave g1 = gauss(128, 64, 16);

assignWaveIndex(1, 2, g1, 100);
assignWaveIndex(1, g1, 150);   // <-- same wave, different chans/index → recon crashes
